gleusercontent.com/-eUocAJBVKCk/ULJ9DWKgdtI/AAAAAAABjf0/otpE5Sv_qi4/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252012%252520-%252520White%252520Rim%252520Trail%252520views%252520-%252520Chip%252520%252526%252520Dale%252520Towers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-eUocAJBVKCk/ULJ9DWKgdtI/AAAAAAABjf0/otpE5Sv_qi4/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252012%252520-%252520White%252520Rim%252520Trail%252520views%252520-%252520Chip%252520%252526%252520Dale%252520Towers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Chip &amp; Dale towers.</i></b><br>\r\r\n				<br>\r\r\n		<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-gcI_7CfVvr8/ULJ9GOIaEsI/AAAAAAABjgA/xQ65ShVQvpE/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252013b%252520-%252520White%252520Rim%252520Trail%252520views%252520-%252520Chip%252520%252526%252520Dale%252520Towers%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-gcI_7CfVvr8/ULJ9GOIaEsI/AAAAAAABjgA/xQ65ShVQvpE/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252013b%252520-%252520White%252520Rim%252520Trail%252520views%252520-%252520Chip%252520%252526%252520Dale%252520Towers%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Chip &amp; Dale towers. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n				<br>\r\r\n		<br>\r\r\nAt last, after several hours of slow dirt road driving, we caught our first glimpse of Washer Woman.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-EFvB5_19QVY/ULJ9L_z5OjI/AAAAAAABjgY/jsLCG2JylGo/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252017a%252520-%252520White%252520Rim%252520Trail%252520views%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520Tower%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-EFvB5_19QVY/ULJ9L_z5OjI/AAAAAAABjgY/jsLCG2JylGo/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252017a%252520-%252520White%252520Rim%252520Trail%252520views%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520Tower%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Washer Woman seen from the East, along the White Rim Trail. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n				<br>\r\r\n		<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-XHQvoXSI6OI/ULJ9Pst7RJI/AAAAAAABjgo/oRV3CLRj4pU/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252021%252520-%252520Islet%252520in%252520the%252520Sky%252520%252526%252520Blocktop.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-XHQvoXSI6OI/ULJ9Pst7RJI/AAAAAAABjgo/oRV3CLRj4pU/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252021%252520-%252520Islet%252520in%252520the%252520Sky%252520%252526%252520Blocktop.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Islet in the Sky &amp; Blocktop Tower, seen from the East.</i></b><br>\r\r\n				<br>\r\r\n		<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-fDoaVn-Qmf4/ULJ9SXekkYI/AAAAAAABjg0/A1ks9x5qKjY/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252021c%252520-%252520Rim%252520Arch%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-fDoaVn-Qmf4/ULJ9SXekkYI/AAAAAAABjg0/A1ks9x5qKjY/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252021c%252520-%252520Rim%252520Arch%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Mesa Arch. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n				<br>\r\r\n		<br>\r\r\nAt least we reached the turn in the road where one parks to approach Washer Woman and Monster Tower. Unfortunately it took us longer than expected to make the drive out here, and the days were very short this time of year, so we decided to relax, hike around, and head up to the tower early the next morning.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-BGwUe2E0GM4/ULJ9WlyEmRI/AAAAAAABjhE/o-sOCkJMqLg/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252024%252520-%252520Sand%252520Castle%25252C%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers%252520from%252520the%252520parking.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-BGwUe2E0GM4/ULJ9WlyEmRI/AAAAAAABjhE/o-sOCkJMqLg/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252024%252520-%252520Sand%252520Castle%25252C%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers%252520from%252520the%252520parking.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sand Castle Tower, Washer Woman, &amp; Monster Tower seen from the SW.</i></b><br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nSo after some lounging we headed up a river wash and ridge to the south to get some nice views of the formations. It was nice being back in this area, as I had mountain biked out to this very spot when I was in high school. Although I had no idea what these formations were, looking back through old photos I found that I had indeed photographed Washer Woman some 12 years ago.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nAs we headed up the ridge, Dirk and admired some of the interesting rock features in the area, like the sandstone imprints of riverbed textures.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-cnrCt1fDHkk/ULJ9ba5knHI/AAAAAAABjhQ/nf4H67NiA2U/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252026a%252520-%252520Sandstone%252520water%252520imprints%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-cnrCt1fDHkk/ULJ9ba5knHI/AAAAAAABjhQ/nf4H67NiA2U/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252026a%252520-%252520Sandstone%252520water%252520imprints%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>				<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sandstone water imprints. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-y8YcjJ6_Qoo/ULJ9dY9PlqI/AAAAAAABjhU/U_7_iTct58Y/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252027%252520-%252520Sandstone%252520water%252520imprints.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-y8YcjJ6_Qoo/ULJ9dY9PlqI/AAAAAAABjhU/U_7_iTct58Y/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252027%252520-%252520Sandstone%252520water%252520imprints.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sandstone water imprints.</i></b><br>\r\r\n				<br>\r\r\n		<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-JI-AtZ6nvqg/ULJ9jMsi0HI/AAAAAAABjho/qeKd7M6p4OU/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252031a%252520-%252520Islet%252520in%252520the%252520Sky%252520%252526%252520Blocktop%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-JI-AtZ6nvqg/ULJ9jMsi0HI/AAAAAAABjho/qeKd7M6p4OU/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252031a%252520-%252520Islet%252520in%252520the%252520Sky%252520%252526%252520Blocktop%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Islet in the Sky &amp; Blocktop Tower, seen from the East. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n					<br>\r\r\n	<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-FaTXB1lolc0/ULJ9lcdA00I/AAAAAAABjhw/IE_USRJCqec/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252032%252520-%252520Sand%252520Castle%25252C%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers%252520from%252520ridge.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-FaTXB1lolc0/ULJ9lcdA00I/AAAAAAABjhw/IE_USRJCqec/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252032%252520-%252520Sand%252520Castle%25252C%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers%252520from%252520ridge.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sand Castle Tower, Washer Woman, &amp; Monster Tower seen from the West.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-NE4KbX8fv5Q/ULJ9nfLSXjI/AAAAAAABjh4/jQ4aYviB1dI/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252034%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520Tower.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-NE4KbX8fv5Q/ULJ9nfLSXjI/AAAAAAABjh4/jQ4aYviB1dI/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252034%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520Tower.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Washer Woman seen from the West.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nIn Search of Suds, the aim for the next day, ascends the thin slanting dark line on the right side of the formation. In fact, one of the pitches goes right trough the tiny triangular arch.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nUnfortunately the cold had sapped the remaining battery power from my camera, and I had left my spare back at the car, so I missed out on some of the best shots of the day. Fortunately Dirk also has an eye for photography.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-efOWnJV_S4I/ULJ9s16BF-I/AAAAAAABjiQ/DKdU4N7WKTs/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252035c%252520-%252520Ridge%252520Boulders%252520%252526%252520towers%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-efOWnJV_S4I/ULJ9s16BF-I/AAAAAAABjiQ/DKdU4N7WKTs/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252035c%252520-%252520Ridge%252520Boulders%252520%252526%252520towers%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>		<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Washer Woman &amp; Monster Tower from the West. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n					<br>\r\r\n	<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Jgrq5m5VIyk/ULJ9trAa4VI/AAAAAAABjiU/ZmOO9K8tPpk/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252035d%252520-%252520Ridge%252520Boulders%252520%252526%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Jgrq5m5VIyk/ULJ9trAa4VI/AAAAAAABjiU/ZmOO9K8tPpk/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252035d%252520-%252520Ridge%252520Boulders%252520%252526%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>			<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Washer Woman from the West. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n					<br>\r\r\n	<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-XA3eEQFMVA0/ULJ9uUtyXNI/AAAAAAABjiY/gYoPxSLVLaM/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252035e%252520-%252520Ridge%252520Boulders%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Tower%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers%252520%252526%252520Mark%252520Thomas.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-XA3eEQFMVA0/ULJ9uUtyXNI/AAAAAAABjiY/gYoPxSLVLaM/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252035e%252520-%252520Ridge%252520Boulders%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Tower%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers%252520%252526%252520Mark%252520Thomas.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Monster Tower from the West. I had wanted to take this shot, but my camera was out of batteries. So I\'m at least taking credit for the idea :-)  (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n					<br>\r\r\n	<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-Ggve3IZTsCo/ULJ9vrC41hI/AAAAAAABjig/0kL3LdTYuHs/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252036a%252520-%252520Sunset%252520silhouette%252520of%252520Islet%252520in%252520the%252520Sky%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-Ggve3IZTsCo/ULJ9vrC41hI/AAAAAAABjig/0kL3LdTYuHs/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252036a%252520-%252520Sunset%252520silhouette%252520of%252520Islet%252520in%252520the%252520Sky%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sunset silhouette of Islet in the Sky and Blocktop Tower. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nWe made it back to the truck just before dark, and enjoyed dinner and beer as the sun set and I played around with taking some night shots.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-u9CaE98krRU/ULJ9wYkoMFI/AAAAAAABjik/1pnoYzXqN6M/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252037%252520-%252520Sand%252520Castle%25252C%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers%252520after%252520sunset.JPG\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-u9CaE98krRU/ULJ9wYkoMFI/AAAAAAABjik/1pnoYzXqN6M/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252037%252520-%252520Sand%252520Castle%25252C%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers%252520after%252520sunset.JPG\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sand Castle Tower, Washer Woman, &amp; Monster Tower seen from the SW at evening with the first few stars showing. (30 sec exposure)</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-fvOJqoyHDes/ULJ9xhEayUI/AAAAAAABjis/USWlO5j9hFE/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252038%252520-%252520Sand%252520Castle%25252C%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers%252520after%252520sunset.JPG\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-fvOJqoyHDes/ULJ9xhEayUI/AAAAAAABjis/USWlO5j9hFE/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252038%252520-%252520Sand%252520Castle%25252C%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers%252520after%252520sunset.JPG\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sand Castle Tower, Washer Woman, &amp; Monster Tower seen from the SW at evening with the first few stars showing. (30 sec exposure)</i></b><br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-h-eNSvOWvzA/ULJ905YuIqI/AAAAAAABji8/H7PzuiRN0Wg/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252040a%252520-%252520Clouds%252520%252526%252520Tower%252520panorama%252520after%252520sunset.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-h-eNSvOWvzA/ULJ905YuIqI/AAAAAAABji8/H7PzuiRN0Wg/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252040a%252520-%252520Clouds%252520%252526%252520Tower%252520panorama%252520after%252520sunset.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Clouds and tower after sunset, with first stars showing. (30 sec exposure)</i></b><br>\r\r\n					<br>\r\r\n	<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Nuv6aMJSddw/ULJ93Lek61I/AAAAAAABjjE/SaZ2BpqqKng/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252042%252520-%252520Star%252520Streaks%252520over%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers.JPG\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Nuv6aMJSddw/ULJ93Lek61I/AAAAAAABjjE/SaZ2BpqqKng/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252042%252520-%252520Star%252520Streaks%252520over%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers.JPG\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sand Castle Tower, Washer Woman, &amp; Monster Tower seen from the SW under a 30 minute exposure.</i></b><br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Rp9qqWuMxlM/ULJ94TbakcI/AAAAAAABjjM/N18xKd3LRkI/s1600/2012-11-14%252520-%25252043%252520-%252520Star%252520Streaks%252520over%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Rp9qqWuMxlM/ULJ94TbakcI/AAAAAAABjjM/N18xKd3LRkI/s800/2012-11-14%252520-%25252043%252520-%252520Star%252520Streaks%252520over%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520%252526%252520Monster%252520Towers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Sand Castle Tower, Washer Woman, &amp; Monster Tower seen from the SW under a 30 minute exposure.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<b><u>November 15 - In Search of Suds</u></b><br>\r\r\n					<br>\r\r\nThe next morning we were up and ready to go much earlier. With the short days it turned out that we had just enough time to do the approach, climb, and descent before dark.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-_aas2_C7x8I/ULJ962n463I/AAAAAAABjjY/m4YtZWfp6NA/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252001a%252520-%252520Sunrise%252520approach%252520to%252520the%252520towers%252520-%2525203%252520Wise%252520Men%252520Shadows%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-_aas2_C7x8I/ULJ962n463I/AAAAAAABjjY/m4YtZWfp6NA/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252001a%252520-%252520Sunrise%252520approach%252520to%252520the%252520towers%252520-%2525203%252520Wise%252520Men%252520Shadows%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>				<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Shadows of Sand Castle Tower, Washer Woman, &amp; Monster Tower seen from the SW at sunrise. These shadows remind me of the Three Wise Men. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n					<br>\r\r\n	<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-nS2M3fpYoQk/ULJ99zCGIWI/AAAAAAABjjk/E3MoTU5_dNI/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252004%252520-%252520SW%252520side%252520of%252520Monster%252520Tower.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-nS2M3fpYoQk/ULJ99zCGIWI/AAAAAAABjjk/E3MoTU5_dNI/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252004%252520-%252520SW%252520side%252520of%252520Monster%252520Tower.jpg\"></a>			<br>\r\r\n<b><i>SW side of Monster Tower on the approach.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-1yn4xImy2Oo/ULJ-DFMDvMI/AAAAAAABjrU/jQwK-Q9IIQQ/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252010%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520from%252520the%252520base.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-1yn4xImy2Oo/ULJ-DFMDvMI/AAAAAAABjrU/jQwK-Q9IIQQ/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252010%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520from%252520the%252520base.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Washer Woman from the base.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-bdVi-ohcAg8/ULJ-E5kt9vI/AAAAAAABjrc/7Ium6vgi3uY/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252012%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520from%252520the%252520base.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-bdVi-ohcAg8/ULJ-E5kt9vI/AAAAAAABjrc/7Ium6vgi3uY/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252012%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520from%252520the%252520base.jpg\"></a>			<br>\r\r\n<b><i>In Search of Suds from the base. The route ascends this corner all the way to the top.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						Pitch 0 is a loose cl. 4-5 pitch that some people rope up for. As it looked loose and it was hard to tell just how tricky it would be, we decided to rope up. I led this pitch, then P1 &amp; P2 as a block, then Dirk led the last 3 pitches to the summit.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ukWCOkO-Wv4/ULJ-Knwtd-I/AAAAAAABj8Q/Z6yQCHYlpE0/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252012b%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P0%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ukWCOkO-Wv4/ULJ-Knwtd-I/AAAAAAABj8Q/Z6yQCHYlpE0/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252012b%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P0%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>			<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Starting approach pitch 0 of \"In Search of Suds\" (cl. 5). (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\nPitch 0 really isn\'t that bad. The toughest part is the first 40 ft, and a rope would not save you from hitting ledges. After that I didn\'t have any need to place pro, keeping things easy by traversing far right to Monster Tower and then walking back along the ridge crest to Washer Woman.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-kCRyavG4ZZE/ULJ-Lfym8HI/AAAAAAABj8U/DFYaoxgB3qQ/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252013%252520-%252520Monster%252520Tower%252520N%252520Ridge%252520from%252520start%252520of%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520on%252520the%252520Washer%252520Woma.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-kCRyavG4ZZE/ULJ-Lfym8HI/AAAAAAABj8U/DFYaoxgB3qQ/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252013%252520-%252520Monster%252520Tower%252520N%252520Ridge%252520from%252520start%252520of%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520on%252520the%252520Washer%252520Woma.jpg\"></a>		<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Monster Tower N Ridge from the start of \"In Search of Suds\".</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nThe first pitch is a really fun 5.9+ to 5.10- corner, with one crux being passing a small roof in the beginning.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-7pzz3lFZEhE/ULJ-NCvRrYI/AAAAAAABj8c/LvHDojZItl4/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252015%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P1%252520first%252520crux.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-7pzz3lFZEhE/ULJ-NCvRrYI/AAAAAAABj8c/LvHDojZItl4/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252015%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P1%252520first%252520crux.jpg\"></a>		<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Leading first 5.9-5.10 section of P1.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-k92RyW6fJ48/ULJ-ObFXltI/AAAAAAABj8g/YukuM0wI8O4/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252015a%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P1%252520first%252520crux%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-k92RyW6fJ48/ULJ-ObFXltI/AAAAAAABj8g/YukuM0wI8O4/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252015a%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P1%252520first%252520crux%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>		<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Leading the first 5.9-5.10 crux of P1. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-k8VB8eCu5zs/ULJ-PQz5U-I/AAAAAAABj8k/qbDtsrwZLYY/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252015aa%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P1%252520first%252520crux%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-k8VB8eCu5zs/ULJ-PQz5U-I/AAAAAAABj8k/qbDtsrwZLYY/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252015aa%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P1%252520first%252520crux%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Leading the first 5.9-5.10 crux of P1. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-D2QTHP5J1Vw/ULJ-RLLENgI/AAAAAAABj8s/KsPEH7L8TuY/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252015c%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P1%252520first%252520crux%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-D2QTHP5J1Vw/ULJ-RLLENgI/AAAAAAABj8s/KsPEH7L8TuY/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252015c%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P1%252520first%252520crux%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Leading the first 5.9-5.10 crux of P1. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nThe roof went easily, but there was another tougher crux next that I was not expecting. A very sandy OW in a flaring corner! I got up as far as I could with my #5 but just could not make the final reach into the hand crack. I backed down and did a combination of liebacking, stemming, and chimneying farther out.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-2sfL4cvMuFw/ULJ-S8gRbUI/AAAAAAABj80/b8A26PRvwi4/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252016%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P1%252520OW%252520rux.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-2sfL4cvMuFw/ULJ-S8gRbUI/AAAAAAABj80/b8A26PRvwi4/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252016%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P1%252520OW%252520rux.jpg\"></a>		<br>\r\r\n<b><i>The second 5.9-5.10 crux of P1 of \"In Search of Suds\". I had to back down this to re-evaluate my strategy before I could get past this strange corner.</i></b><br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\nAbove the wide, the terrain quickly eased to 5.7 climbing. There are a lot of loose blocks on this section, so the leader should take care to stem and chimney up most of this pitch and NOT grab or stand on the blocks.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-KXt1VCzjUjo/ULJ-UQEG19I/AAAAAAABj84/kfNdy2AIaLg/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252017%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Looking%252520down%252520P1%252520loose%2525205_7%252520blocks-chimney.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-KXt1VCzjUjo/ULJ-UQEG19I/AAAAAAABj84/kfNdy2AIaLg/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252017%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Looking%252520down%252520P1%252520loose%2525205_7%252520blocks-chimney.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Looking down the 5.7 corner and loose blocks of P1.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nI set up a belay on a comfy ledge just beneath the mini-arch.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-WzG3bo4FMqc/ULJ-W7KVN0I/AAAAAAABj9A/vGi4ds_ghyI/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252018a%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%252520Eye%252520of%252520the%252520Needle%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-WzG3bo4FMqc/ULJ-W7KVN0I/AAAAAAABj9A/vGi4ds_ghyI/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252018a%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%252520Eye%252520of%252520the%252520Needle%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>P2 \"Eye of the Needle\". (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nI set off on P2, which requires climbing <i>into </i>the arch, and stemming up it until it is easy to enter the chimney inside of it.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-TU_GEIQsJYk/ULJ-X_RUflI/AAAAAAABj9E/nk_9LLJ3hZw/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252019%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%252520Threading%252520the%252520Eye%252520of%252520the%252520Needle.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-TU_GEIQsJYk/ULJ-X_RUflI/AAAAAAABj9E/nk_9LLJ3hZw/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252019%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%252520Threading%252520the%252520Eye%252520of%252520the%252520Needle.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>P2 looking down as I am threading the \"Eye of the Needle\".</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-h4K3mLGBVKw/ULJ-aGB93vI/AAAAAAABj9I/xSzonr0M2dM/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252020%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%2525205_7%252520chimney.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-h4K3mLGBVKw/ULJ-aGB93vI/AAAAAAABj9I/xSzonr0M2dM/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252020%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%2525205_7%252520chimney.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>P2 5.7 chimney, full of loose chockstones. I did a lot of different techniques to avoid pulling on these, as they would have fallen on Dirk!</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-R2Tosm8rO3k/ULnWyyf44GI/AAAAAAABj9Q/T7BXQgRoFp4/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252020b%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%252520Threading%252520the%252520Eye%252520of%252520the%252520Needle%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-R2Tosm8rO3k/ULnWyyf44GI/AAAAAAABj9Q/T7BXQgRoFp4/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252020b%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%252520Threading%252520the%252520Eye%252520of%252520the%252520Needle%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>P2 entering the 5.7 chimney after passing through the little arch. I\'m stemming the arch to avoid the loose chockstones in the chimney. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Cy9jbDWFaLk/ULJ-bbleG2I/AAAAAAABj9Y/S1K12jCqVm4/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252021%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%252520looking%252520down%2525205_7%252520Chimney%252520%252526%252520Needle%252520Eye.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Cy9jbDWFaLk/ULJ-bbleG2I/AAAAAAABj9Y/S1K12jCqVm4/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252021%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%252520looking%252520down%2525205_7%252520Chimney%252520%252526%252520Needle%252520Eye.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>P2 looking down the \"Eye of the Needle\" and onto Dirk as I am in the 5.7 chimney.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nThe next crack was very strange, but clean and interesting. This steep section gradually transitions into a corner, which widens into an OW, and finishes with a 5.9+ to 5.10- mantle onto the belay ledge.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-mWs1OEM_EyI/ULJ-cjkyJiI/AAAAAAABj9c/SU5Na3kx_Ns/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252022%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%2525205_7-5_8%252520cracks.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-mWs1OEM_EyI/ULJ-cjkyJiI/AAAAAAABj9c/SU5Na3kx_Ns/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252022%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%2525205_7-5_8%252520cracks.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>P2 5.7-5.8 cracks.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-bWu2CaI2Ybc/ULnW0XyDJNI/AAAAAAABj9k/pxIyM_dZ2ho/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252022b%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%2525205_7-5_8%252520cracks%252520w%2525205_9%252520OW%252520above%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-bWu2CaI2Ybc/ULnW0XyDJNI/AAAAAAABj9k/pxIyM_dZ2ho/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252022b%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P2%2525205_7-5_8%252520cracks%252520w%2525205_9%252520OW%252520above%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Leading the P2 5.7-5.8 cracks, with the 5.9 OW seen above. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-XcHwmkTpXYA/ULJ-f69VgPI/AAAAAAABj9s/9VTW1RRA86k/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252022cc%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P2%2525205_9%252520OW-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-XcHwmkTpXYA/ULJ-f69VgPI/AAAAAAABj9s/9VTW1RRA86k/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252022cc%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Leading%252520P2%2525205_9%252520OW-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Leading the P2 5.9 OW. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\nThe OW is a squeeze lower down, so I dealt with this feature by crawling inside to place a large cam, then shimmied back out to lieback the rest, as there is a good edge and good feet features to use.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nI finished by perhaps being the first person to do the P2 mantle with my belly facing up! (Or at least I sure hope I am. It was not pretty). I really didn\'t like the exposure, lack of feet, and a sandy, flat mantling ledge with nothing to pull on, so I just kept stemming until it got too wide, then I pressed my shoulder into the ledge as I walked my feet up and slid my torso onto the ledge, where I then rolled over and did the beached whale dance to the anchors.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-7qPPA-1awBc/ULJ-hLRKeDI/AAAAAAABj98/mFDpKrBzPcE/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252023%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Looking%252520down%252520P2.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-7qPPA-1awBc/ULJ-hLRKeDI/AAAAAAABj98/mFDpKrBzPcE/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252023%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Looking%252520down%252520P2.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Looking down P2.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-EZMh4n1_grs/ULJ-jfhx5XI/AAAAAAABj-Q/hfw4EYeysRs/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252025%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520following%252520P2%252520nearing%252520the%252520OW.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-EZMh4n1_grs/ULJ-jfhx5XI/AAAAAAABj-Q/hfw4EYeysRs/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252025%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520following%252520P2%252520nearing%252520the%252520OW.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Dirk following P2, nearing the 5.9 OW.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-r-ZfNzoSvuo/ULnX7R1tqHI/AAAAAAABj-U/3p_VCsyctqw/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252026%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520following%252520P2%252520reaching%252520the%2525205_9Plus%252520Mantle.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-r-ZfNzoSvuo/ULnX7R1tqHI/AAAAAAABj-U/3p_VCsyctqw/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252026%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520following%252520P2%252520reaching%252520the%2525205_9Plus%252520Mantle.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Dirk following P2, at the 5.9+ mantle finish. On lead I didn\'t dare finish this as Dirk is doing (feet are poor for this and the ledge is sandy). Instead I did a full-body stem and mantled onto my back before flipping into \'beached whale\' position.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Tl2oOu1ZKXM/ULJ-kOH_JcI/AAAAAAABj-s/9SU0rQJQozc/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252027%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520White%252520Rim%252520seen%252520from%252520atop%252520P2.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Tl2oOu1ZKXM/ULJ-kOH_JcI/AAAAAAABj-s/9SU0rQJQozc/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252027%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520White%252520Rim%252520seen%252520from%252520atop%252520P2.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>The White Rim seen from atop P2 of \"In Search of Suds\".</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nFinally it was Dirk\'s turn, and not a moment too soon. This beast needed to be unleashed!<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-gut7ChfL4og/ULJ-m25IIqI/AAAAAAABj-8/9CBwjXIoF4M/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252029%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P3%252520from%252520P2%252520belay.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-gut7ChfL4og/ULJ-m25IIqI/AAAAAAABj-8/9CBwjXIoF4M/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252029%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P3%252520from%252520P2%252520belay.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>P3 seen from P2 belay.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-yZ0KssL5EFM/ULJ-ni0CweI/AAAAAAABj_A/BRoqSPBXGiU/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252030%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520starting%252520in%252520to%252520P3.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-yZ0KssL5EFM/ULJ-ni0CweI/AAAAAAABj_A/BRoqSPBXGiU/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252030%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520starting%252520in%252520to%252520P3.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Dirk starting into P3 (5.10+).</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-bHVOtNNI_-c/ULJ-og4nGeI/AAAAAAABj_E/yMBywfHaHHE/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252031%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520leading%252520P3.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-bHVOtNNI_-c/ULJ-og4nGeI/AAAAAAABj_E/yMBywfHaHHE/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252031%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520leading%252520P3.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Dirk leading P3 (5.10+). Monster Tower is behind.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nThe pitch takes good gear, and the 5.10+ section is a one-move wonder. However, the move is very awkward, physical, and committing as you transition from the crack to some strange crimping and face climbing around and over a small roof.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ihUbWSK5zWM/ULJ-qlxpUuI/AAAAAAABj_M/B9n1NfPoelk/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252031b%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Following%252520P3%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ihUbWSK5zWM/ULJ-qlxpUuI/AAAAAAABj_M/B9n1NfPoelk/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252031b%252520-%2