20atop%252520P3.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-pwOimHNsnEE/ULJ-wi9zvPI/AAAAAAABj_k/UssxWv0gmdI/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252035%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520The%252520White%252520Rim%252520from%252520atop%252520P3.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>The White Rim from atop P3.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-bNbUJKQYvdE/ULJ-xhhIbGI/AAAAAAABj_o/O6yqt3o-pjs/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252036%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P4%252520tower%252520traverse.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-bNbUJKQYvdE/ULJ-xhhIbGI/AAAAAAABj_o/O6yqt3o-pjs/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252036%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P4%252520tower%252520traverse.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>P4 tower traverse.</i></b><br>\r\r\n			<br>\r\r\n			<br>\r\r\nThe next pitch was a 4th class scramble along a knife-edge ridge, with a short 5.9 finger crack in a step to overcome at the end.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ZQ8EMm5TTss/ULJ-zTFPSfI/AAAAAAABj_0/n3ssN3m02yk/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252038%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Following%252520P4%252520tower%252520traverse.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ZQ8EMm5TTss/ULJ-zTFPSfI/AAAAAAABj_0/n3ssN3m02yk/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252038%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Following%252520P4%252520tower%252520traverse.jpg\"></a><br>\r\r\n<b><i>Following the P4 traverse (cl. 4).</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-MkJ4S3t4OTU/ULnW3JJNiHI/AAAAAAABj_8/8IKAPdUm6m8/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252038b%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Following%252520P4%252520tower%252520traverse%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-MkJ4S3t4OTU/ULnW3JJNiHI/AAAAAAABj_8/8IKAPdUm6m8/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252038b%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Following%252520P4%252520tower%252520traverse%252520-%252520by%252520Dirk%252520Summers.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Following the P4 tower traverse. Monster Tower and the White Rim are behind. (by Dirk Summers)</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-0hcr5em7DoQ/ULJ-0flAp5I/AAAAAAABkAA/_FCjhjlJNpI/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252039%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P4%2525205_9%252520headwall.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-0hcr5em7DoQ/ULJ-0flAp5I/AAAAAAABkAA/_FCjhjlJNpI/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252039%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P4%2525205_9%252520headwall.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>5.9 headwall at the end of P4.</i></b><br>\r\r\n					<br>\r\r\n	<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-0cBzHxV6T2A/ULJ-1DwSlMI/AAAAAAABkAI/Lufn7LNIYhg/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252040%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520atop%252520P4%252520with%252520Monster%252520Tower.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-0cBzHxV6T2A/ULJ-1DwSlMI/AAAAAAABkAI/Lufn7LNIYhg/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252040%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520atop%252520P4%252520with%252520Monster%252520Tower.jpg\"></a>	<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Dirk atop P4 with Monster Tower &amp; the White Rim behind.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nThe last pitch is the crux of the climb. Depending on who you ask, it is either a very hard 5.10+ (much harder than the other 5.10+ pitch), or a 5.11- face climb protected by some drilled angles and bolts. The first 5.9 bit to reach the first bolt was said to be runout on loose rock.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-3LViLagCGNg/ULJ-3PyTzTI/AAAAAAABkAQ/GbaVNOg-hJI/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252042%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P5%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520Head.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-3LViLagCGNg/ULJ-3PyTzTI/AAAAAAABkAQ/GbaVNOg-hJI/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252042%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520P5%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520Head.jpg\"></a>		<br>\r\r\n<b><i>P5 Washer Woman head (5.11-).</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\nThere was some loose rock, but apart from ledges to hit, the section didn\'t seem \'R\' rated as you were never that far out from pro. Dirk made it looks pretty leisurely.<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-SHnWBSSBws4/ULJ-4MakOXI/AAAAAAABkAc/xUYX3Znqk4I/s1600/2012-11-15%252520-%25252043%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520casually%252520placing%252520pro%252520on%252520P5.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-SHnWBSSBws4/ULJ-4MakOXI/AAAAAAABkAc/xUYX3Znqk4I/s800/2012-11-15%252520-%25252043%252520-%252520Washer%252520Woman%252520-%252520In%252520Search%252520of%252520Suds%252520-%252520Dirk%252520casually%252520placing%252520pro%252520on%252520P5.jpg\"></a>		<br>\r\r\n<b><i>Dirk casually placing pro on P5.</i></b><br>\r\r\n						<br>\r\r\n<br>\r\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-FD0Bs4U5F_I/